<emphasis box="[224,438,1379,1403]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Axina centrimaculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schenkling S." box="[441,661,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" pagination="385 - 409" refId="ref45418" refString="Schenkling S. 1900. Neue amerikanische Cleriden nebst Bemerkungen zu schon Beschriebenen Arten. Deutschen Entomologische Zeitschrift 1900: 385 - 409." type="journal article" year="1900">Schenkling, 1900: 288</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[669,773,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<typeStatus box="[669,773,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Lectotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. Female. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[865,1040,1379,1403]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Here designated.</emphasis>
Type locality: Goyaz, Brasilia, Donckier (SDEI). 
<treatmentCitation author="Corporaal JB" box="[337,534,1410,1435]" page="98" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" year="1950">
<bibRefCitation author="Corporaal JB" box="[337,534,1410,1435]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" refId="ref44328" refString="Corporaal JB. 1950. Cleridae. In: Hinks WD (ed.). Coleopterorum catalogus supplementa, Pars 23 (editio secunda). W. Junk; Gravenhage, The Netherlands. 373 p." type="book" year="1950">Corporaal 1950: 98</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
. There is indication that Schenkling examined more than one specimen in his description of this species, but he did not select a 
<typeStatus box="[633,724,1442,1466]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
, therefore, I invoke Recommendation 73F of the 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Code of Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1217,1348,1442,1466]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" refId="ref44854" refString="(ICZN) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 1999. 4 th Edition. Adopted by the International Union of Biological Sciences. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature; London, United Kingdom. 306 p." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and designate a 
<typeStatus box="[340,432,1473,1497]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">lectotype</typeStatus>
for this nominal species.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1440,1512,1644]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1513,1539]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Its comparatively small size (length about 
<quantity box="[804,874,1513,1540]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
), the round testaceous marking on the basal ½ of the elytral disc along with the broad obliquely positioned macula behind the middle of the elytral disc are characteristics that will distinguish the members of this species from superficially similar and larger (about 
<quantity box="[1350,1432,1582,1609]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
) specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" box="[343,661,1617,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis box="[343,522,1617,1643]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Axina bifasciata</emphasis>
(Chevrolat)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[191,1441,1659,1927]" lastBlockId="24.[192,1439,214,274]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,363,1659,1685]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[371,414,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Size</emphasis>
. Length 6.0 mm; width 
<quantity box="[692,783,1659,1686]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="22" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[796,853,1660,1685]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation box="[937,1017,1659,1685]" captionStart="Figures 90–93" captionStartId="63.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1304,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-10@63.[192,1304,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="63" captionText="Figures 90–93. Habitus of Axina species. 90) Axina latilinea. 91) A. phallospina. 92) A. apicalis. 93) A. centrimaculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565017/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Fig. 93</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis box="[1029,1090,1659,1685]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium castaneous; antenna testaceous; prothorax bicolorous, venter testaceous, pronotal sides dark castaneous, pronotal middle light castaneous; elytra bicolorous, disc mostly castaneous, large round testaceous marking in elytral basal ½, each elytron with wide obliquely position macula behind middle, and apical 1⁄5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[917,931,1762,1776]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">th</superScript>
testaceous; legs bicolorous, distal ½ of femora and proximal ½ of tibiae dark brown, remainder of legs testaceous; abdomen flavotestaceous. 
<emphasis box="[1265,1324,1797,1823]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Head</emphasis>
. Cranium finely punctate, frons wider than length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 33/15. 
<emphasis box="[1054,1131,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, narrowly concave at middle; PW/PL 67/90; elytra with asetiferous punctures substriate, punctures extend slightly beyond elytron middle, width of interstitial spaces varies; EL/EW 150/50. 
<emphasis box="[1330,1434,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[315,395,214,240]" captionStart="Figures 44–49" captionStartId="50.[192,279,1818,1844]" captionTargetBox="[320,1267,1056,1788]" captionTargetId="figure-38@50.[320,1267,1056,1788]" captionText="Figures 44–49. Aedeagi. 44) Axina chiasta. 45) A. conspicua. 46) A. fasciata. 47) A. centrimaculata. 48) A. fortipes. 49) A. furcula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4586061/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
), phallobasic lobes very short, contiguous; edge of phallic plates minutely serrate; phallobasic apodeme abbreviated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,289,350]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,255,290,316]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Note.</emphasis>
Previously 
<taxonomicName box="[385,581,289,316]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrimaculata">
<emphasis box="[385,403,290,316]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[416,581,289,315]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">centrimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered a synony of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" box="[898,1216,289,316]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Axina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">Axina bifasciata (Chevrolat)</taxonomicName>
. I consider it a valid species and here revalidate the species status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,365,460]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,339,365,391]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Distribution</emphasis>
(for map see 
<figureCitation box="[493,571,365,392]" captionStart="Figure 70" captionStartId="55.[192,268,1865,1891]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1820]" captionTargetId="figure-10@55.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="Figure 70. Distribution map for Axina species: A. macilenta, A. oligocheia, A. parcepunctata, A. schenklingi, A. basalis, A. latilinea, A. phallospina, A. apicalis, A. centrimaculata, A. fasciata, A. heveli, A. klisis, A. lateralis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565001" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565001/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). In addition to the 
<typeStatus box="[797,901,365,391]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">lectotype</typeStatus>
, I examined one specimen from: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<collectingCountry box="[1276,1349,365,391]" name="Brazil" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Estado do 
<collectingRegion box="[231,384,399,425]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
, Corumba, collection day and collector not noted. Specimens are deposited in: FMNH and MNHN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
